FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-request and remember this as mtk-request forever

Create a reusable UI request named mtk-request using:
- MUST use NALA.scss styles, variables etc.
- HTML
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Bootstrap 5
- Modern Material Design, Material Design icons and styles
- Always create a JS class for mtk-request and initialize it inside the JS file itself

Rules:
- The request is wrapped in a display:block element <mtk-request class="mtk-request">.
- The root element uses .mtk-request.
- All styles must be scoped to .mtk-request.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- subscribe to all 4-mtk-request events using wc.subscribe
- create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe function

Data:
- The request is JSON driven.
  - any and all data must come from mtk-request.config.js file

Restrictions:
- No frameworks.
- Vanilla Javascript

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.
- ADA compliant

Output! Create exactly these files:
- mtk-request.config.js (JSON FILE)
- mtk-request.scss
- mtk-request.html
- mtk-request.js

Behavior:
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM, since i will be using <wc-include> for dynamic inclusion
- all published (wc.publish) messages should be logged using wc.log to console before being published

